From Lawrence D'Oliveiro Waikato University Subject Re Interesting ADB behaviour on In article I said I know that plugging and unplugging ADB devices with the power on is not supported and you can hit problems if you have multiple devices with clashing addresses and all I've had a couple of e mail responses from people who seem to believe that this sort of thing is not only unsupported it is downright I have heard of no such warnings from anybody at Just to be sure I asked a couple of our technicians one of whom has been servicing Macs for There is no danger of damaging logic boards by plugging and unplugging ADB devices with the power SCSI yes ADB Lawrence D'Oliveiro fone Computer Services Dept fax University of Waikato electric mail Hamilton New Zealand ' S ' E GMT